video.title: Dark Matter
video.synopsis: After waking up aboard a derelict spaceship with no memories, the crew of the Raza investigates the mystery of their identities and destination.

episodes.synopsis: When the crew of a derelict ship awakens with no memories, they soon discover that they're ferrying arms to an off-world colony of rebels.
episodes.title: Episode 1

episodes.synopsis: The crew faces a difficult dilemma: abandon the miners to certain defeat and death, or assist them against insurmountable odds.
episodes.title: Episode 2

episodes.synopsis: Paranoia takes over when the ship mysteriously drops out of faster-than-light speed, suggesting possible sabotage by one of the crew.
episodes.title: Episode 3

episodes.synopsis: Lacking funds, the crew decides to dock at a space station and sell some of their weapons, but the past comes back to haunt several of them.
episodes.title: Episode 4

episodes.synopsis: Assigned to salvage a freighter, the crew is thrown into a pitched battle with the zombie-like denizens of the abandoned ship.
episodes.title: Episode 5

episodes.synopsis: Five volunteers to endure a chemically induced hypnosis to retrieve the crew's stored memories, but she becomes trapped in a dream-like state.
episodes.title: Episode 6

episodes.synopsis: When the ship's vault is opened, Three comes face-to-face with his past, while One is distracted by a new entertainment-model android.
episodes.title: Episode 7

episodes.synopsis: While the ship is docked for refueling and repairs, Six tries to locate a man from his past in order to get revenge. One discovers his true identity.
episodes.title: Episode 8

episodes.synopsis: When Four disappears from the ship following a space station stopover, the crew must make a choice: rescue their fellow crew member or abandon him.
episodes.title: Episode 9

episodes.synopsis: Commander Truffault rescues the crew from an attack but assigns them to steal a mysterious device from a research station, aided by mercenaries.
episodes.title: Episode 10

episodes.synopsis: The crew of the "Raza" battles their former mercenary partners for control of the ship, while their enemies try to extract information from One.
episodes.title: Episode 11

episodes.synopsis: A rescue and retrieval operation at a remote research facility becomes a dangerous and surprising homecoming for one member of the crew.
episodes.title: Episode 12

episodes.synopsis: Tensions are dangerously high as the search for a traitor jeopardizes friendships among the crew and leads to some long-held secrets being revealed.
episodes.title: Episode 13

episodes.synopsis: After a stunning betrayal, the crewmates wake up in a detention facility. One investigates his wife's murder. Six asks Five to crack a coded file.
episodes.title: Welcome to Your New Home

episodes.synopsis: As Chief Inspector Shaddick pressures them to confess their crimes, Two, Three and Four hatch a daring plan to escape from Hyperion-8.
episodes.title: Kill Them All

episodes.synopsis: When the Android attempts to repair her neural link, three crew members suddenly collapse -- and wake up as they were before the memory wipe.
episodes.title: I’ve Seen the Other Side of You

episodes.synopsis: During a resupply stop, Three encounters his old crew and learns more about his past. Arax hunts for a valuable item. The Android makes new friends.
episodes.title: We Were Family

episodes.synopsis: To help the team track down One's attacker, the Android goes undercover as a human and tries to get arrested by the Galactic Authority.
episodes.title: We Voted Not to Space You

episodes.synopsis: As the crew looks for a way to drum up cash, Nyx suggests a raid on a freighter carrying a pricey street drug. But she has a hidden agenda.
episodes.title: We Should Have Seen This Coming

episodes.synopsis: To unlock the secret of the key card, the team infiltrates Alicia Reynaud's headquarters. Devon opens up about a traumatic incident from his past.
episodes.title: She’s One of Them Now

episodes.synopsis: The blink drive misfires, transporting the Raza to a parallel world where the shipmates encounter alternate versions of themselves.
episodes.title: Stuff to Steal, People to Kill

episodes.synopsis: When Two's nanites begin to fail, the crew heads to Dwarf Star Technologies in search of a cure and learns new details about her creation.
episodes.title: Going Out Fighting

episodes.synopsis: The Android confesses to the crew that she may be malfunctioning. But strange occurrences aboard the ship soon reveal a larger threat.
episodes.title: Take the Shot

episodes.synopsis: At a planetary outpost, Three scrambles to rescue Five from local criminals while Kierken and his cloned soldiers hunt the rest of the crew.
episodes.title: Wish I’d Spaced You When I Had the Chance

episodes.synopsis: Using the blink drive, Four builds an alliance and sets out to reclaim Ishida Ryo's throne. But the mission takes a harrowing turn.
episodes.title: Sometimes in Life You Don’t Get to Choose

episodes.synopsis: As the crew races to thwart an attack on a corporate summit and prevent an intergalactic war, a familiar face complicates their plans.
episodes.title: But First, We Save the Galaxy

episodes.synopsis: Separated during the blast at the space station, the surviving crew members face daunting obstacles as they try to make their way back to the Raza.
episodes.title: Being Better Is So Much Harder

episodes.synopsis: After boarding a secret Ishida station to retrieve the blink drive, Two, Three and Six are caught in a space void. Five gets lost in her memories.
episodes.title: It Doesn't Have to Be Like This

episodes.synopsis: When a distress call leads the crew to a colony locked in a standoff with Traugott Corp, Two and Six argue over whether to intervene.
episodes.title: Welcome to the Revolution

episodes.synopsis: Three struggles to convince the others that he's stuck in a time loop, reliving the same day over and over -- and over -- again.
episodes.title: All the Time in the World

episodes.synopsis: When Tabor's girlfriend is taken hostage by a business rival, Adrian and the crew search for a file that may contain valuable secrets.
episodes.title: Give It Up, Princess

episodes.synopsis: The crewmates square off once more against their doppelgängers from the alternate reality, who've been busy stirring up trouble.
episodes.title: One Last Card to Play

episodes.synopsis: As Six recovers from a neurotoxin attack, flashbacks to another life and strange encounters with the team leave him questioning his reality.
episodes.title: Wish I Could Believe You

episodes.synopsis: Leaders of the rebel colonies seek refuge aboard the Raza after an attack by Ferrous Corp. Five notices the Android acting strangely.
episodes.title: Hot Chocolate

episodes.synopsis: When the blink drive whisks the crew 600 years back in time, they visit Earth in search of help. But blending in proves tricky.
episodes.title: Isn't That a Paradox?

episodes.synopsis: The team helps the Android's friend Victor track down the scientist behind the upgrade, who has a surprising link to a member of the Raza crew.
episodes.title: Built, Not Born

episodes.synopsis: While investigating an anomaly at a Dwarf Star Technologies lab, Three is plagued by disturbing sensations.
episodes.title: Thee Dwarf Star Conspiracy

episodes.synopsis: As Three, Five and Six try to negotiate Two's return, Ryo reveals details from the crew's past, and the Android uncovers a secret.
episodes.title: My Final Gift to You

episodes.synopsis: With help from Teku, the crew discovers the location of the Ferrous shipyard. But their plan to destroy it takes an unexpected turn.
episodes.title: Nowhere to Go
